# **IMPORTANT!** вАФ don't forget to add the event hook to the form XML file.
The file is usually named `Form.xml` in the parent directory of the module code.

Event hooks in XML look like:

```xml
<Events>
	<Event name="OnOpen">–Я—А–Є–Ю—В–Ї—А—Л—В–Є–Є</Event>
	<Event name="BeforeWrite">–Я–µ—А–µ–і–Ч–∞–њ–Є—Б—М—О</Event>
	<Event name="OnCreateAtServer">–Я—А–Є–°–Њ–Ј–і–∞–љ–Є–Є–Э–∞–°–µ—А–≤–µ—А–µ</Event>
</Events>
```

Common form events (this is a **non-exhaustive subset** вАФ the platform exposes dozens of form, item, and table events):

| XML Event Name | Russian Handler Name | Description |
|----------------|----------------------|-------------|
| `OnOpen` | `–Я—А–Є–Ю—В–Ї—А—Л—В–Є–Є` | Client, when form opens |
| `OnClose` | `–Я—А–Є–Ч–∞–Ї—А—Л—В–Є–Є` | Client, when form closes |
| `BeforeWrite` | `–Я–µ—А–µ–і–Ч–∞–њ–Є—Б—М—О` | Client, before write |
| `AfterWrite` | `–Я—А–Є–Ч–∞–њ–Є—Б–Є` | Client, after write |
| `OnCreateAtServer` | `–Я—А–Є–°–Њ–Ј–і–∞–љ–Є–Є–Э–∞–°–µ—А–≤–µ—А–µ` | Server, form creation |
| `BeforeWriteAtServer` | `–Я–µ—А–µ–і–Ч–∞–њ–Є—Б—М—О–Э–∞–°–µ—А–≤–µ—А–µ` | Server, before write |
| `AfterWriteAtServer` | `–Я—А–Є–Ч–∞–њ–Є—Б–Є–Э–∞–°–µ—А–≤–µ—А–µ` | Server, after write |
| `OnReadAtServer` | `–Я—А–Є–І—В–µ–љ–Є–Є–Э–∞–°–µ—А–≤–µ—А–µ` | Server, when reading object |

The value inside the `<Event>` tag is the name of the handler procedure in the form module.

## Getting the full event list

For the complete and authoritative list of available events, do **not** rely on this table. Use:

- `bsl_scope_members` with `member_type="events"` and the relevant context (e.g. `"–£–њ—А–∞–≤–ї—П–µ–Љ–∞—П–§–Њ—А–Љ–∞"`, `"–Я–Њ–ї–µ–§–Њ—А–Љ—Л"`, `"–Ґ–∞–±–ї–Є—Ж–∞–§–Њ—А–Љ—Л"`, `"–Ъ–љ–Њ–њ–Ї–∞–§–Њ—А–Љ—Л"`).
- `inspect_form_layout` on a similar existing form вАФ every wired-up event is listed under each element with its handler name.
- `docinfo` / `docsearch` against the platform documentation for the specific form-item type.
- `search_forms` to locate canonical examples that already use the event you need.
